										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>As I write this series, and all other period stories, I end up doing a huge load of research along the way.  I enjoy this part of the process quite a lot because of all the interesting little nuggets of awesome that I stumble upon.  I love finding out things that I didn&#8217;t even know I didn&#8217;t know.  Since I&#8217;m sure you will find this entertaining as well, I&#8217;m going to blog about all of my discoveries, and anything thing else Twist or Steampunk related, right here.  Enjoy!  You lucky person, you.</p>
<h4 style="text-align:center;">&#8211; Monthly Blog Schedule &#8211;</h4>
<ul>
<li>1st Sunday: <a href="http://clockworktwist.com/category/picture-day/">Picture day!</a> <span style="color:#808080;"> </span><span style="color:#808080;">Steampunk art and artists.</span></li>
<li>2nd Sunday: Random post.  <span style="color:#808080;"><a href="http://clockworktwist.com/category/did-you-know/">Did you know</a>,  <a href="http://clockworktwist.com/category/twisty-things/">Twist info</a>,  <a href="http://clockworktwist.com/category/indie-publishing/">indie pub</a>, etc,.</span></li>
<li>3rd Sunday: <a href="http://clockworktwist.com/category/suggested-reading/">Suggested Reading! </a> <span style="color:#808080;">Steampunk book review.</span></li>
<li>4th Sunday: Random post again. <span style="color:#888888;"> Same as 2nd Mondays.</span></li>
<li>5th Sunday: <a href="http://clockworktwist.com/category/anyone-for-a-game/">Anyone for a game?</a>  <span style="color:#808080;">Steampunk game review.</span></li>
</ul>
<p>Are you an artist/writer/photographer/sculptor/gamer/poet who loves Steampunk as much as I do?   Would you like to see your work featured on this blog?  Or, do you know of someone else who’s work you adore?  Please leave a comment below with a link or two!   I’ll happily feature anything that I think will fit the style of my blog, or even anything that&#8217;s just plain awesome.</p>
